metadata.name: Life's Vortex
metadata.description:
Out the window,
And into the skies with the birds,
Where she always said she belonged,
I kept her in a coffin, killed her curiosity, 
But it wasn’t enough....!
I looked into the skies and she was gone,
Shattering the flower vase, 
Just like my life, 
A life that wasn’t mine, 
A life that is a lie....!
